# Ag02  AMS01     GeV  1/m2/sr/MeV       flux   0.265  0.22   0.31    154.e-2 13.4e-2  0.0   a    0.00  0.00   0.0 | 1.01  0.0   0.0 Table 4.8 linear sum errors
# ACEW  CRIS      MeV  1/cm2/sr/MeV      ratio 188.0 114.   310.      4.22e-2 0.36e-2  0.0   a   13.26  0.00   0.0 |13.-1  0.0   0.0
# |     |         |                      |      |      |     |        |      |         |     |   |                 |                 |
# | Reference key (4 characters) from which data was taken,  as in table at end
#       | Experiment name (or acronym to distinguish different results from same experiment)
#                 | units  (energy per nucleon) (MeV,GeV)
#                      | units of flux (cm2,m2/MeV,GeV)
#                                        | type of measurement: flux (for spectra e.g. for elements) or ratio (e.g. for B/C)
#                                               | mean energy as given by authors or computed from low,high
#                                                      | low energy of range
#                                                            | high energy of range
#                                                                     | flux or ratio value
#                                                                             | error bar -
#                                                                                       |error bar + (if 0.0 assumed symmetrical)
#                                                                                            | type of measurment: a=absolute, r=ratio
#                                                                                                | secondary Z.A if ratio: up to 3 values to be combined.
#                                                                                                  A=-1 means all A for given Z e.g. 13.-1=Al elemental
#                                                                                                                  | primary Z.A if ratio, or isotope Z.A if spectrum
#                                                                                                                    up to 3 values to be combined
#                                                                                                                    A=-1 means all A for given Z e.g. 13.-1=Al elemental
#                                                                                                                                   | free for comments on this entry
#
